"title": "5087: David, reign of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5087: david, reign of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>David reigned over Judah for seven and a half years and over all Israel for 33 years. He extended the kingdom to the boundaries promised by God to Joshua.</p>\n<h2>David reigned over Judah in Hebron</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:4\">2SA 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:8-2Sam2:11\">2SA 2:8–2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:1\">2SA 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:12-2Sam3:21\">2SA 3:12–3:21</a></p>\n<h2>David reigned over Israel in Jerusalem</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3-2Sam5:10\">2SA 5:3–5:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:1-1Chr11:9\">1CH 11:1–11:9</a></p>\n<h2>David extended the boundaries of the kingdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:6\">2SA 8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:17-2Sam5:25\">2SA 5:17–5:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr14:8-1Chr14:17\">1CH 14:8–14:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:1-2Sam8:14\">2SA 8:1–8:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:1-1Chr18:13\">1CH 18:1–18:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:1-2Sam10:19\">2SA 10:1–10:19</a></p>\n<h2>David's kingship</h2>\n<h3>He ruled justly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:15\">2SA 8:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:1-2Sam9:11\">2SA 9:1–9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:3-2Sam23:4\">2SA 23:3–23:4</a></p>\n<h3>His problems with his children</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:1-2Sam13:21\">2SA 13:1–13:21</a></p>\n<h3>Absalom's conspiracy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:10\">2SA 15:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:13-2Sam15:18\">2SA 15:13–15:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:1-2Sam18:17\">2SA 18:1–18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:28-2Sam18:33\">2SA 18:28–18:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:4-2Sam19:8\">2SA 19:4–19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:1-Ps3:8\">PSA 3:1–3:8</a></p>\n<h3>David's mightiest warriors were called ``the Thirty''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:13-2Sam23:17\">2SA 23:13–23:17</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:15-1Chr11:19\">1CH 11:15–11:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:24-2Sam23:39\">2SA 23:24–23:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:26-1Chr11:47\">1CH 11:26–11:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:20-2Sam23:23\">2SA 23:20–23:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:23-1Chr11:25\">1CH 11:23–11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:4\">1CH 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:16-1Chr12:18\">1CH 12:16–12:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:5-1Chr27:6\">1CH 27:5–27:6</a></p>\n<h3>The struggle against the northern supporters of Saul</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:1\">2SA 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>The revolt led by Sheba</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:1-2Sam20:22\">2SA 20:1–20:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The census of Israel and Judah</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:1-2Sam24:17\">2SA 24:1–24:17</a></p>\n<h2>Solomon succeeds David despite the claims of Adonijah</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:5-1Kgs1:53\">1KI 1:5–1:53</a></p>\n<h2>The death of David</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:10-1Kgs2:12\">1KI 2:10–2:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:26-1Chr29:28\">1CH 29:26–29:28</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:1-2Sam23:7\">2SA 23:1–23:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:1-1Kgs2:9\">1KI 2:1–2:9</a></p>",
